data.text: We don’t need centrism to win out, both sides are not equally bad, sure one side has confronted politicians while they eat and vandalized the offices of senators, the other side sends bombs to politicians they disagree with and celebrities who are to vocal about politics.

He’s tried to divide us from the start of his political career and for decades before. Attacking the media immediately after a bomb was sent to one of the orgs he’s been most vocally against ought to shock me. Voting might solve a piece of the problem but it’s not going to fix it
